.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE EGGNOG1 L "11 Dec 85" 1986
.RZ "GRANDMA'S SWINGIN' EGGNOG" "A potent holiday party eggnog drink"
Eggnog is a traditional holiday party drink. This recipe makes a rich and
powerful eggnog.
.IH "Serves 20"
.IG "6" "egg yolks"
.IG "1/2 cup" "sugar" "100 g"
(white granulated)
.IG "2 cups" "milk" "500 ml"
.IG "2 cups" "light rum" "500 ml"
.IG "2 cups" "whipping cream" "500 ml"
.PH
.SK 1
Beat yolks until light. Add sugar and mix well. Add milk and rum.
Mix well, then chill for at least 3 hours.
.SK 2
One hour before serving, whip cream and stir into chilled
mixture. Return to refrigerator for an hour.
.SK 3
Serve in punch cups and dust with nutmeg.
.NX
This stuff is POTENT, even if you reduce the rum by half.
Brandy, dark rum or bourbon may be substituted for the light rum. If
you prefer a nonalcoholic eggnog, leave out the booze
altogether. With or without booze, this eggnog is very rich, and very
good.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
5 minutes preparation, 3 or more hours cooling.
.I Precision:
approximate measurement OK.
.WR
Suzanne Barnett-Scott
Calcomp Sauders Display Products Division, Scottsdale, Arizona
